Bash.sh - Framework for easy Shell Scripting
============================================

This is a framework intended to created shell scripts in an
easy way. It has functions that help to parse command line arguments
and work with arrays for now.

New ideas and contributions are welcome. Report the issues in the GitHub page.

Example of usage:

    #!/bin/bash
	# app.sh
	source ./bang.sh
	 
	# Help flag
	bang.add_flag --help "Show this help"
	bang.add_alias --help -h
	# Message
	bang.add_opt --msg "Message to be printed!"
	bang.add_alias --msg -m
	# Output
	bang.add_flag --stderr "Redirects the message to stderr"
	 
	bang.required_args "--msg"
	 
	bang.init "$@"
	 
	if bang.has_flag? --help; then
		bang.show_usage
	else
		bang.check_required_args
		msg="Your message is: $(bang.getopt --msg)"
		cmd="echo"
		bang.has_flag? --stderr && cmd="print_e"
		$cmd "$msg"
	fi

No arguments:
	$ ./app.sh
	The program was aborted due an error:
	 
		Option '--msg' is required and was not specified

Showing usage:
	$ ./app.sh -h # ou ./app.sh --help
	 
	Showing script usage:
	 
	Options:
	--msg|-m <value>        (Required) Message to be printed!
	Flags:
	--help|-h        Show this help
	--stderr         Redirects the message to stderr

Prints to STDOUT
	$ ./app.sh --msg "Hello World" # ou ./app.sh -m "Hello World"
	Your message is: Hello World

Prints to STDERR
	$ ./app.sh --msg "Hello World" --stderr 1>/dev/null
	Your message is: Hello World
